description.0: Toro and the Human Torch face the evil scientist named Bashon, who has a full artillery of machinery to level cities of innocent people...
description.5: The Torch and young Toro are captured near the Canadian border! Escaping is one thing, but flying back to New York City before impending disaster is another!
description.7: Private Steve Rogers and Bucky Barnes join forces with American soldiers to defeat the Japanese in New Guinea.
description.24: Prince Namor gets the opportunity to join the United States Marines!
description.25: The Flaming Duo seeks to find an undercover Nazi who is poisoning United States soldiers with cyanide...
description.30: Good Ol' Mass Transit! Torch and Toro find themselves on a broken down bus in an unfamiliar town.
description.31: The mighty Sub-Mariner vs. a group of Pirate Zombies!? We wouldn't lie to you -- read this issue!
description.32: Mock Mikado and his army invade the United States, and Private Steve Rogers puts the kibosh on their assault at stage one!
description.37: The Human Torch becomes even more powerful! The only downside? He is fully under the control of villains!
description.38: Betty Ross is kidnapped by the followers of the Hooded Horror. Plus, an underwater city, Captain America, Bucky and more!
description.41: The Sub-Mariner is on vacation by the river, but you know someone is going to interrupt his brief time off...
description.42: The Human Torch and Toro are riding the subway in New York City, when a dangerous armed Nazi begins to threaten everyone's safety!
description.45: The Vulture and his goons take Bucky and it's up to Captain America to rescue his sidekick.
description.46: You thought Captain America was the most patriotic super hero?! Meet Major Liberty!
description.48: Toro and The Torch take to the seas! Whom will they find lurking beneath the ocean's murky depths?
description.49: Prince Namor battles the men of Imperial Japan during the height of WWII.
description.51: Who is the League of Unicorns and who do they have in their crosshairs?
description.54: A U-Boat is actively sinking American vessels, and the Navy is powerless against it. Enter the mighty Sub-Mariner!
description.55: Dr. Crime and his gang of criminals run amock and it's up to Captain America and Bucky to put an end to their tyranny.
description.56: Captain America and Bucky are accused of murder. Can they clear their names and stop the real killer?
description.58: Professor John Wolf may have an invention that will shift the tides of the war! Unfortunately, it may fall into the wrong hands...
description.60: Another hero joins the ranks of Marvel's Golden Age greats -- CITIZEN V! Plus, more tales of Marvel's pioneers like The Thunderer, Silver Scorpion, Captain Daring, and more!
description.61: When a secret weapon is being transported, Captain America and Bucky are tasked with defending it but the Countess has other plans.
description.62: Torch goes undercover as a criminal to seek the origin of recent illegal arms trafficking.
description.63: A mysterious artist paints portraits that portray the death of the person looking at it. Once they take a glance at it, their death is written in stone. What will Captain America do about this terrifying, otherworldly phenomenon?
description.66: It's horror in the suburbs as the killer White Death strikes!
description.67: Who is the deadly Ra? The duo of Captain America and Bucky aim to find out.
description.68: Witness the Nazi fightin', crime stoppin' super hero in his first ever appearance! Captain Terror!
description.70: The Sub-Mariner hurls around a giant torpedo against his enemies!
description.74: The Red Skull returns and he's looking for revenge on his former minions who have failed him. Can Captain America and Bucky stop him?
description.77: The Sub-Mariner takes a bullet to the head! We know he's strong, but can even Namor survive such an attack?
description.78: The Human Torch & Toro are on vacation, but a knife-throwing murderer interrupts their relaxation!
description.81: Introducing the first class of Golden Age heroes! In this issue, the origin of Defender and The Whizzer!
description.87: The Human Torch and Sub-Mariner battle it out in a fight to the death!
description.88: The mighty Sub-Mariner shoves a torpedo down the Nazi's submarine hatch!
description.89: The original Human Torch, Captain America, and his commandos take on traitors to the war effort in this debut issue!
description.92: The Human Torch cleverly uses Toro as bait, but will setting that same bait come back to bite him?
description.93: The Sub-Mariner faces perhaps the most evil enemy the world has ever seen. The Nazis attempt to undermine and conquer an underwater village, but will have to get through the Prince of Atlantis first!
description.96: Another collection of Marvel's earliest heroes! Featuring The Thunderer, The Challenger, Captain Daring, and more!
description.98: What better way to introduce a hero clad in the American flag during World War II than by showing him decking Hitler? Simple and effective, we have Joe Simon and Jack Kirby to thank for this one.

22.text: In Egypt, Steve and Bucky learn Colonel Fitzpatrick was murdered because he was studying the Tomb of the Witch Queen.  After entering the tomb they discover findings on a mummified child which leads to a battle with the masked Spawn of the Witch Queen.

27.text: Steve and Bucky find themselves in a forest swamp near a plantation mansion where a violent crocodile attacks.

28.text: Steve and Bucky join other soldiers at Gigo's new bowling alley, where he learns some balls are specially equipped to injure players.

35.text: Dr. Weirdler tests a newly discovered serum that reanimates dead bodies and places the brain of an executed criminal named Killer Kole in a deceased gorilla.  After the gorilla’s grave is struck by lightning, he is revived and he begins to terrorize the city.

37.text: The Human Torch becomes even more powerful! The only downside? He is fully under the control of villains!

48.text: Toro and The Torch take to the seas! Whom will they find lurking beneath the ocean's murky depths?

57.text: The Torch and Toro stop a murder spree! The Sub-Mariner battles a ghost ship! And the Vision clashes with a soul-stealing scientist!

59.text: The adventures of Marvel's first generation of heroes continue! Torch and Toro, Namor, the Angel and more pave the way to the Marvel Age of Comics!

62.text: Torch goes undercover as a criminal to seek the origin of recent illegal arms trafficking.

64.text: Even more amazing tales from the early days of Marvel! Starring the Human Torch, Namor the Sub-Mariner, and the Golden Age Vision!

69.text: A collection of Marvel's Golden Age greats! Human Torch, Sub-Mariner, the original Ka-Zar and Vision, and more!

73.text: More incredible tales of action and mystery from the Golden Age of Marvel featuring the Human Torch & Toro, the Sub-Mariner, and many more!

75.text: Captain America battles the Camera Fined and his Darts of Doom in one of his earlies adventures!

76.text: More incredible tales of action and mystery from the Golden Age of Marvel featuring the Human Torch & Toro, the Sub-Mariner, and many more!

80.text: Captain America and the Ringmaster of Death!  Can Cap put an end to his villainy?

82.text: More incredible tales of action and mystery from the Golden Age of Marvel featuring the Human Torch & Toro, the Sub-Mariner, and many more!

83.text: More incredible tales of action and mystery from the Golden Age of Marvel featuring the Human Torch & Toro, the Sub-Mariner, and many more!

84.text: If the Golden Age heroes don’t pay up, New York City may go up in a smoke by an arsonist’s plot! Even Torch gets scorched by this one!

86.text: Captain America and Bucky face off against the Unholy Legion in a Golden Age classic tale!

90.text: It’s Lights Out for New York City! The Human Torch and Toro realize that a temporary blackout may spell disaster for the New York Stock Exchange!

91.text: Cap and Bucky take the fight right to the Red Skull and his cronies!

92.text: The Human Torch cleverly uses Toro as bait, but will setting that same bait come back to bite him?

94.text: Captain America and Bucky must battle a group of ageless monsters from the East who cannot be killed!

95.text: A collection of Marvel's Golden Age greats! Human Torch, Sub-Mariner, the original Ka-Zar and Vision, plus many more!

97.text: Get ready for a battle epic straight from the Golden Age of Marvel! The Human Torch and Sub-Mariner fight side-by-side once more, against the menace of the European Axis Powers!

98.text: What better way to introduce a hero clad in the American flag during World War II than by showing him decking Hitler?  Simple and effective, we have Joe Simon and Jack Kirby to thank for this one.
